# Messaging System Fixes

Fix duplicate messages (2x) and cross-chat leakage in the WhatsApp messaging module.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> I will be switching to conversation-specific rooms for real-time messages. This will improve performance and eliminate cross-chat leakage.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Backend Components

#### [MODIFY] [socket.gateway.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/common/gateways/socket.gateway.ts)
- Add room support for specific conversations.
- Deduplicate emissions where possible.

#### [MODIFY] [messaging.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/messaging/messaging.service.ts)
- Refine message emission logic.
- Separate "list update" events from "new message" events for better isolation.
- Use conversation rooms for `new_message` events.

---

### Frontend Components

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/app/(app)/messages/page.tsx)
- Join/Leave conversation rooms on selection.
- Improve message deduplication in [handleSendMessage](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/app/%28app%29/messages/page.tsx#101-110) and socket listeners.
- Prevent race conditions between API response and socket events.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- No specific automated tests exist for sockets currently, but I will verify via browser interactions.

### Manual Verification
1.  Open two tabs with the same user.
2.  Send a message from Tab A.
3.  Verify Tab A shows 1 message (no duplicate).
4.  Verify Tab B shows 1 message.
5.  Switch to a different conversation in Tab B and verify messages from the first conversation do not appear there.
